Oscar GC
========

Oscar GC is a custom distribution of Goose, an open-source agent platform.
See LICENSE for license terms (Apache License, Version 2.0).

This product includes software developed by the following projects:

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Goose
Copyright 2024 Block, Inc.
Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
https://github.com/aaif-goose/goose (formerly https://github.com/block/goose)

Oscar GC forks Goose as a custom distribution under upstream's
CUSTOM_DISTROS.md. The Rust agent core remains substantially upstream;
the desktop UI (`ui/desktop/src/`) and sibling MCP servers
(`oscar-onboarding-mcp`, `oscar-memory-mcp`) are Oscar GC additions.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

claude-for-legal
Copyright Anthropic, PBC.
Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
https://github.com/anthropics/claude-for-legal

The contents of `skills/in-house-legal/` are vendored from Anthropic's
claude-for-legal open-source repository. Sprint 11 pulled at:

  Upstream commit: 4d55f53962293ab0ec0dcfad84c51afb54535975
  Upstream date:   2026-05-15
  Pull date:       2026-05-18

Nine in-house practice-area plugins are vendored:
ai-governance-legal, commercial-legal, corporate-legal,
employment-legal, ip-legal, litigation-legal, privacy-legal,
product-legal, regulatory-legal.

See `skills/in-house-legal/NOTICE` for per-plugin attribution detail.
Per-file provenance comments appear at the top of each vendored
SKILL.md (`<!-- Sourced from anthropics/claude-for-legal/<plugin> @
<sha>; Apache 2.0 -->`).

